    "description": "Felodipine is a calcium channel blocker that is primarily used to treat high blood pressure (hypertension) and certain types of angina (chest pain). By inhibiting the influx of calcium ions into the vascular smooth muscle and cardiac muscle, Felodipine causes relaxation of the blood vessels, leading to a decrease in blood pressure and reduction of workload on the heart.",
    "uses": "Felodipine is mainly prescribed for the management of hypertension, helping to lower blood pressure in patients with essential hypertension. It may also be used for the treatment of chronic stable angina, as it helps to improve blood flow and reduce the frequency and severity of angina attacks. Additionally, Felodipine may be prescribed for certain off-label uses, such as treating certain types of arrhythmias and conditions where blood flow is compromised.",
